SIMPLE: fishtail
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: fishtail
<hw>fishtail</hw> <pos>v. t.</pos> <fld>(aeronautics)</fld> <def>to slow
down by moving the tail sideways, of an airplane.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>fishtail</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: fishtail
<hw>fishtail</hw> <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>to have the rear end skid from
side to side, out of control: -- said of automobiles or other
vehicles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Fish-tail burner</b></col>, <cd>a gas burner that gives a
spreading flame shaped somewhat like the tail of a fish.</cd> --
<col><b>Fish-tail propeller</b></col> <fld>(Steamship)</fld>, <cd>a
propeller with a single blade that oscillates like the tail of a fish
when swimming.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fishwife</ent>⟦br⟧
